1
00:00:00,580 --> 00:00:02,890
So...

2
00:00:02,892 --> 00:00:04,877
what is it you wanted to ask me?

3
00:00:04,877 --> 00:00:08,637
What are your priorities in life?

4
00:00:08,637 --> 00:00:11,150
My life?

5
00:00:11,694 --> 00:00:13,627
What?

6
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:17,247
Sorry, sounds like I'm too intrusive?

7
00:00:17,247 --> 00:00:19,220
Is it like, a coverage report interview?

8
00:00:19,220 --> 00:00:20,968
Coverage report interview?

9
00:00:20,968 --> 00:00:22,777
Well, an interview, I guess?

10
00:00:22,777 --> 00:00:27,461
I thought I'd know more about you so I can better support you in going independent.

11
00:00:27,461 --> 00:00:29,129
You'll give me your support?

12
00:00:29,129 --> 00:00:32,450
- Thank you so much.
- No, it's the least I can do.

13
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:38,939
So, between work, money, love, and marriage...

14
00:00:38,939 --> 00:00:41,509
how important are they, honestly?

15
00:00:41,509 --> 00:00:44,311
In order of priority?

16
00:00:45,383 --> 00:00:50,117
Well, considering which one I can relate to...

17
00:00:50,117 --> 00:00:55,422
but then, I don't really know what it is exactly that I relate to.

18
00:00:55,422 --> 00:00:59,745
Maybe something that matters most to you?

19
00:00:59,745 --> 00:01:02,462
Right now, that will be my work.

20
00:01:02,462 --> 00:01:05,054
Yup, going independent is the most important thing to me right now.

21
00:01:05,054 --> 00:01:07,007
You're currently dating someone, right?

22
00:01:07,007 --> 00:01:08,736
Yes.

23
00:01:08,736 --> 00:01:11,104
But he's fine with me putting my work first.

24
00:01:11,104 --> 00:01:15,512
A relationship won't last if both parties place their expectations on a date.

25
00:01:17,853 --> 00:01:20,156
Well understood.

26
00:01:20,156 --> 00:01:22,382
So, I've to help you succeed in going independent.

27
00:01:22,382 --> 00:01:25,185
It's still sketchy, but I've come up with a startup plan.

28
00:01:25,185 --> 00:01:26,341
Already?

29
00:01:26,341 --> 00:01:28,395
Thank you so much.

30
00:01:28,395 --> 00:01:34,494
Firstly, until you can open a studio, you'll need to achieve a fixed number of your own customers.

31
00:01:34,494 --> 00:01:40,584
For that, I'd suggest that you teach yoga online, using this carbon neutral panel.

32
00:01:40,584 --> 00:01:42,272
It's a fixed cost, so there's some risk.

33
00:01:42,272 --> 00:01:45,130
Carbon neutral panel?

34
00:01:45,705 --> 00:01:48,076
Take a look at this.

35
00:01:48,076 --> 00:01:50,277
Thank you.

36
00:01:52,130 --> 00:02:00,020
credits

37
00:02:01,584 --> 00:02:04,925
To have a date with no expectations...

38
00:02:06,842 --> 00:02:10,030
is it even possible?

39
00:02:13,494 --> 00:02:15,401
Huh? Do I have a cold?

40
00:02:16,091 --> 00:02:17,412
I guess not.

41
00:02:17,412 --> 00:02:19,762
Higashimura-san, can I have a word?

42
00:02:19,762 --> 00:02:24,015
- Sure.
- It's about Hinata Akari-san.

43
00:02:24,015 --> 00:02:28,703
She wishes to have a marriage meeting with your client.

44
00:02:28,703 --> 00:02:30,384
Here.

45
00:02:32,219 --> 00:02:33,495
Huh?

46
00:02:33,495 --> 00:02:36,905
Sensei, you gave a great speech in today's lecture.

47
00:02:36,905 --> 00:02:39,794
Is that so? The content is the same as usual, though.

48
00:02:39,794 --> 00:02:43,558
Yes. I didn't really quite get it before,

49
00:02:43,558 --> 00:02:47,278
but it finally got through to me today. I wonder why?

50
00:02:47,278 --> 00:02:49,144
Well...

51
00:02:49,144 --> 00:02:52,710
I give my speeches with the belief that no matter how boring my lecture is,

52
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:55,954
there may be just one person in the theater who'll find it interesting.

53
00:02:55,954 --> 00:03:00,247
I see. It's like talking to an invisible girlfriend in the theater, right?

54
00:03:00,247 --> 00:03:01,730
Looks like your marriage hunting is going smoothly.

55
00:03:01,730 --> 00:03:03,793
No, not necessarily so.

56
00:03:03,793 --> 00:03:06,954
What about you,  Kodama-san? How was it with that Sam guy?

57
00:03:06,954 --> 00:03:09,370
Sam faded out of the picture, in the end.

58
00:03:09,370 --> 00:03:15,229
That guy is all about the environment and human rights, it's tiring to be with him.

59
00:03:15,229 --> 00:03:17,431
That's what I mean. Sustainability fatigue.

60
00:03:17,431 --> 00:03:20,167
Sustainable fatigー
<i>[You may have sustainable fatigue!]</i>

61
00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:22,158
Sustainable fatigue!

62
00:03:22,158 --> 00:03:26,759
It's fatigue arising from trying to achieve sustainability.

63
00:03:26,759 --> 00:03:28,742
What?

64
00:03:28,742 --> 00:03:32,541
A contradiction between sustainability and being tired?

65
00:03:32,541 --> 00:03:35,086
This is interesting!

66
00:03:43,702 --> 00:03:47,279
Hello? Hi, Higashimura-san.

67
00:03:47,279 --> 00:03:48,860
Yes.

68
00:03:51,607 --> 00:03:53,307
What?!

69
00:03:53,307 --> 00:03:57,437
"Good evening Hinata-sama."

70
00:03:57,437 --> 00:04:02,552
"Regarding the marriage meeting,

71
00:04:02,552 --> 00:04:06,578
I was extremely surprised."

72
00:04:06,578 --> 00:04:12,036
"Is this for the purpose of practicing..."

73
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:18,080
"Palpitation".

74
00:04:18,080 --> 00:04:20,671
"Pounding of the heart after running

75
00:04:20,671 --> 00:04:23,797
or when one is nervous".

76
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:33,898
<i>[Sawada Rintaro]</i>

77
00:04:35,396 --> 00:04:37,637
<i>Hello?</i>

78
00:04:37,637 --> 00:04:39,489
Good evening. This is Sawada.

79
00:04:39,489 --> 00:04:41,802
<i>Are you free to talk right now?</i>

80
00:04:41,802 --> 00:04:45,809
If this is regarding the marriage meeting, let us talk about it when we meet.

81
00:04:45,809 --> 00:04:48,767
<i>Or during our walking session.</i>

82
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:49,777
Oh, h-huh?

83
00:04:49,777 --> 00:04:52,106
I humbly request for that. Thank you for understanding.

84
00:04:52,106 --> 00:04:54,843
- <i>Goodbye.</i>
- Waitー

85
00:05:04,008 --> 00:05:06,072
Dad?

86
00:05:08,025 --> 00:05:11,179
Huh? Dad?

87
00:05:11,179 --> 00:05:12,916
What?

88
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:14,515
Jeez...

89
00:05:14,515 --> 00:05:16,650
Turn the lights on, at least.

90
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:18,719
For a moment, I thought you'd fainted.

91
00:05:18,719 --> 00:05:21,171
You're right.

92
00:05:21,171 --> 00:05:24,805
I'm at this age where people worry if I don't turn the lights on.

93
00:05:24,805 --> 00:05:27,240
It's not possible, indeed.

94
00:05:29,796 --> 00:05:31,384
Augh... Kyoka.

95
00:05:31,384 --> 00:05:34,202
I'm asking this for my own reference.

96
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:43,210
When a younger woman and I have a marriage meeting and she marries me, what charmー

97
00:05:44,138 --> 00:05:47,081
What qualities do I have that made it possible?

98
00:05:49,192 --> 00:05:51,516
- None.
- I'm sure there's something.

99
00:05:51,516 --> 00:05:53,652
You need aged care in future,

100
00:05:53,652 --> 00:05:57,825
and before that, you have zero ability in housework.

101
00:05:57,825 --> 00:05:59,493
You have a job,

102
00:05:59,493 --> 00:06:02,405
but your salary and inheritance are so-so.

103
00:06:02,405 --> 00:06:05,265
Besides, you have a daughter in tow, who's single.

104
00:06:05,265 --> 00:06:07,605
No qualities at all, huh?

105
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:13,683
Let me ask, then. What if I say...

106
00:06:13,683 --> 00:06:17,487
I want to marry someone who has a kid. What would you think?

107
00:06:18,846 --> 00:06:20,857
- My, my, my...
- A kid?

108
00:06:20,857 --> 00:06:24,114
- What?!
- A... A...
- You all right?

109
00:06:24,114 --> 00:06:24,999
A kid?

110
00:06:24,999 --> 00:06:29,156
Like I said, "what if"! Just "what if."

111
00:06:29,156 --> 00:06:32,632
Gosh... that...

112
00:06:32,632 --> 00:06:35,360
I will be worried.

113
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:38,899
That's because... you'll be a mom.

114
00:06:40,401 --> 00:06:43,404
But I definitely don't object

115
00:06:43,404 --> 00:06:46,476
to having more family members.

116
00:06:48,098 --> 00:06:53,072
Meeting with people, be it children or seniors,

117
00:06:53,072 --> 00:06:57,700
opens you to a new and bigger world. So I'll give you my blessing.

118
00:06:58,540 --> 00:07:00,576
Dad...

119
00:07:02,298 --> 00:07:05,704
The parents of that young lady whom you're meeting?

120
00:07:05,704 --> 00:07:08,352
It'll be great if they give you their blessings too.

121
00:07:08,352 --> 00:07:10,852
What nonsense are you talking about?

122
00:07:15,448 --> 00:07:18,838
A new world, huh?

123
00:07:20,831 --> 00:07:29,660
<i>[Is Love Sustainable?]
[Episode 8]</i>

124
00:07:36,366 --> 00:07:45,472
♪ <i>Head, shoulders, knees and toes, knees and toes</i> ♪

125
00:07:45,472 --> 00:07:47,400
Hayate Sensei!

126
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:50,804
Nijiro! Long time no see!

127
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:53,440
<i>Hayate Sensei! You're back!</i>

128
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:56,161
Big Brother Hayate!

129
00:07:56,161 --> 00:07:58,145
Sorry that I took such a long break.

130
00:07:58,145 --> 00:07:59,605
I was nearby.

131
00:07:59,605 --> 00:08:00,666
Please accept these.

132
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:04,977
Wow, that's a lot! Thank you!

133
00:08:04,977 --> 00:08:07,388
Hayate Sensei, when will you come back?

134
00:08:07,388 --> 00:08:12,303
The week after next. I've started on a different job, so I can't come every day, though.

135
00:08:12,303 --> 00:08:14,494
Aw, bummer...

136
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:18,977
Then can I go to your house and play next time?

137
00:08:18,977 --> 00:08:23,570
About that... I've moved out from Kyoka-chan's place.

138
00:08:23,570 --> 00:08:25,978
Really?

139
00:08:25,978 --> 00:08:32,373
But I had been telling Kyoka-chan nice things about you so that she's impressed.

140
00:08:32,373 --> 00:08:33,630
You met Kyoka-chan?

141
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:38,941
Yup! She came to my house and made curry. It was delicious.

142
00:08:38,941 --> 00:08:40,752
Is that so?

143
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:44,123
So that's what it was.

144
00:08:47,594 --> 00:08:51,065
Thanks, Nijiro. I'll work hard at it.

145
00:08:51,805 --> 00:08:56,355
I'm sure I still stand a chance.

146
00:08:57,736 --> 00:08:59,921
So you're leaving the studio this month?

147
00:08:59,921 --> 00:09:03,629
Yup. I'm clearing my leave.

148
00:09:03,629 --> 00:09:06,951
I'll first rent a room for my lessons and secure customers.

149
00:09:06,951 --> 00:09:10,150
The consultant told me to conduct online lessons on the internet.

150
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:11,718
She's a nice person.

151
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:15,155
I see. Things will get busier for you.

152
00:09:15,813 --> 00:09:17,173
What about you, Seita?

153
00:09:17,173 --> 00:09:20,969
There'll be more marriage meetings during the bridal season, so I'll be busier.

154
00:09:20,969 --> 00:09:26,700
So... my dad has resumed his marriage hunting?

155
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:29,704
Lately, he's been acting suspiciously.

156
00:09:32,539 --> 00:09:35,692
I'm really curious to find out, but you can't tell me, right?

157
00:09:35,692 --> 00:09:39,135
I really want to tell you, but I can't.

158
00:09:39,135 --> 00:09:41,915
Excuse me, here's your green curry.

159
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:44,160
Thanks.

160
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,852
Thank you.

161
00:09:45,852 --> 00:09:50,657
Sorry, I said I'd bring you to eat something you like, but it's still curry in the end.

162
00:09:50,657 --> 00:09:54,738
Well, I'm starting to like curry lately.

163
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:58,733
Welcome to the profound world of curry.

164
00:10:00,618 --> 00:10:03,953
To a new world.

165
00:10:03,953 --> 00:10:06,017
- Huh?
- Nothing.

166
00:10:06,017 --> 00:10:09,309
I mean, I'll leave my dad in your care.

167
00:10:09,309 --> 00:10:12,229
I'll do my best to take care of him.

168
00:10:13,991 --> 00:10:18,275
So, I guess the both of us are going to be quite busy.

169
00:10:18,275 --> 00:10:20,927
Just put your work first, Kyoka-san.

170
00:10:20,927 --> 00:10:23,790
You, too, should put Nijiro-kun first.

171
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,400
We are second in place.

172
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,584
Okay.

173
00:10:26,584 --> 00:10:30,379
No need to bother about me.

174
00:10:32,718 --> 00:10:35,605
It's hard to <i>not</i> bother.

175
00:10:39,338 --> 00:10:41,478
What's that look for?

176
00:10:43,283 --> 00:10:46,295
- Let's dig in.
- Let's dig in!

177
00:11:09,737 --> 00:11:12,839
You could have just let Nijiro stay over at my place tonight.

178
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:15,285
But you have an online meeting with New York in the wee hours.

179
00:11:15,285 --> 00:11:17,267
It'll be hard to wake up in the morning.

180
00:11:17,267 --> 00:11:20,012
Hey, hey, help me pull out the blanket.

181
00:11:21,548 --> 00:11:24,380
- Okay.
- All right, thanks.

182
00:11:27,154 --> 00:11:29,727
Don't be so considerate to your ex-wife.

183
00:11:29,727 --> 00:11:31,991
And don't be too considerate to your girlfriend too.

184
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:33,527
Huh?

185
00:11:38,966 --> 00:11:43,603
Look, I don't really mind if you remarry.

186
00:11:44,577 --> 00:11:47,246
As long as you're properly prepared for it.

187
00:11:47,774 --> 00:11:50,309
I don't plan to remarry.

188
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:56,038
Then don't do anything that will confuse Nijiro.

189
00:11:56,038 --> 00:11:58,256
Confuse him?

190
00:11:59,619 --> 00:12:03,145
The other day, I saw you with your girlfriend

191
00:12:03,145 --> 00:12:05,277
in front of our house.

192
00:12:05,277 --> 00:12:08,594
<i>My phone! Sorry about that.</i>

193
00:12:12,063 --> 00:12:14,753
You shouldn't let a child meet someone who has no plans to get married.

194
00:12:14,753 --> 00:12:18,419
- No, it's not what you thinkー
- You'll wake him up.

195
00:12:32,477 --> 00:12:34,518
You see,

196
00:12:35,206 --> 00:12:37,690
actually,

197
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:43,496
I've been asked to handle an international expo project in Osaka.

198
00:12:44,736 --> 00:12:46,740
Three years.

199
00:12:48,565 --> 00:12:51,638
I haven't given my reply, of course.

200
00:12:51,638 --> 00:12:53,349
Are you going?

201
00:12:53,349 --> 00:12:55,500
Can I go?

202
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:58,084
And leave him to you?

203
00:13:06,264 --> 00:13:09,267
I mean, will it be okay for me to go?

204
00:13:12,928 --> 00:13:14,573
If I go to Osaka,

205
00:13:14,573 --> 00:13:18,376
there's no such thing as leaving Nijiro to me two days a week.

206
00:13:22,518 --> 00:13:26,406
Well, you should also discuss with your girlfriend,

207
00:13:26,406 --> 00:13:28,543
and think it through.

208
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:31,650
Let me know your decision.

209
00:13:31,650 --> 00:13:33,229
Got it.

210
00:13:36,375 --> 00:13:37,748
See you.

211
00:14:03,543 --> 00:14:05,217
Yes?

212
00:14:05,826 --> 00:14:06,993
Hayate!

213
00:14:06,993 --> 00:14:08,860
I'm back!

214
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:10,360
Ha!

215
00:14:10,984 --> 00:14:13,189
It's been a while since I got punched.

216
00:14:13,189 --> 00:14:15,253
What are you happy about?

217
00:14:15,253 --> 00:14:17,850
I was wondering whether it's worth moving out.

218
00:14:17,850 --> 00:14:19,865
Where did you go, exactly?

219
00:14:19,865 --> 00:14:22,328
You suddenly up and went, without telling me and Dad.

220
00:14:22,328 --> 00:14:26,424
Sorry. The pipes in my apartment have already been repaired.

221
00:14:26,424 --> 00:14:29,275
So I brought my luggage on the way to France.

222
00:14:29,275 --> 00:14:32,555
I see. Glad to see you're doing great.

223
00:14:39,323 --> 00:14:41,472
- You're a manager at a hotel?
- Yes.

224
00:14:41,472 --> 00:14:43,080
How did you end up with that job?

225
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:47,022
The parents of a university friend of mine run a hotel chain in France,

226
00:14:47,022 --> 00:14:48,221
and I was invited over.

227
00:14:48,221 --> 00:14:51,325
- Ah, your friend from UCLA?
- That's right.

228
00:14:51,325 --> 00:14:54,068
They have a subsidiary hotel in Malaysia,

229
00:14:54,068 --> 00:14:57,030
and need someone to be stationed there to manage its reopening

230
00:14:57,030 --> 00:15:00,678
as a working vacation hotel. And they said I was the perfect person for the job.

231
00:15:00,678 --> 00:15:03,269
I see. That's amazing.

232
00:15:03,269 --> 00:15:05,959
I had been staying in Malaysia.

233
00:15:05,959 --> 00:15:09,572
But we're reopening next year, so I came back to Japan to recruit staff.

234
00:15:09,572 --> 00:15:10,781
Which explains my attire.

235
00:15:10,781 --> 00:15:13,230
Hayate, you look really capable.

236
00:15:13,230 --> 00:15:15,560
You've fallen for me even more now, right?

237
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,019
You idiot.

238
00:15:17,019 --> 00:15:18,766
Thanks.

239
00:15:25,459 --> 00:15:28,695
To be honest, one day,

240
00:15:28,695 --> 00:15:33,300
I hope to build a school in Malaysia, for homeless kids from less-privileged families.

241
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:36,457
I'm using this hotel job as a stepping stone for that.

242
00:15:36,457 --> 00:15:39,562
I didn't know that you had such big plans.

243
00:15:39,562 --> 00:15:42,308
You were the one who triggered that idea in me.

244
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:46,399
When we were kids, I spent happy times at your place.

245
00:15:46,399 --> 00:15:49,154
That was how I could stay as a kid.

246
00:15:51,984 --> 00:15:54,257
It's all thanks to Aunt.

247
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:02,024
Want to join me?

248
00:16:02,024 --> 00:16:03,922
Sure, I'll go.

249
00:16:03,922 --> 00:16:07,818
That's not what I mean. It's a hotel meant for long-term stayovers,

250
00:16:07,818 --> 00:16:11,730
so it's fully furnished with childcare and proper wellness facilities.

251
00:16:12,247 --> 00:16:14,423
There are yoga classes too.

252
00:16:15,341 --> 00:16:20,013
It's definitely my dream to teach yoga in a southern country,

253
00:16:20,013 --> 00:16:24,011
but right now, I have to first establish my base in Tokyo.

254
00:16:24,011 --> 00:16:26,055
I guess so.

255
00:16:26,689 --> 00:16:30,940
But if you have any problems, feel free to call me anytime.

256
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:34,392
I'll always put you as my first priority.

257
00:16:34,392 --> 00:16:36,450
Hayate.

258
00:16:36,450 --> 00:16:39,718
Whether it's your phone or anything else, I'll fly over to look for it.

259
00:16:39,718 --> 00:16:43,470
Seems like you'll have a hard time without me around.

260
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:46,396
Oh, I've brought souvenirs.

261
00:16:50,187 --> 00:16:54,213
- For you.
- Wow, thanks.

262
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:59,218
Rock salt! And...

263
00:17:01,331 --> 00:17:03,557
Wow... chocolates.

264
00:17:03,557 --> 00:17:05,350
Give me your hand.

265
00:17:07,426 --> 00:17:09,329
Kyoka-chan...

266
00:17:15,053 --> 00:17:18,454
Huh? Wait a minute, Hayate. I...

267
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:28,746
What?

268
00:17:40,352 --> 00:17:43,032
It'll be easier for you to find your phone.

269
00:17:43,694 --> 00:17:45,598
Thank you.

270
00:17:46,705 --> 00:17:50,003
- It suits you.
- Bling, bling, bling.

271
00:17:50,003 --> 00:17:52,641
I'm sorry.
<i>[LED Tokyo]</i>

272
00:17:54,351 --> 00:17:55,686
This is Sawada-san.

273
00:17:55,686 --> 00:17:58,475
I'm Sawada Kyoka. Nice to meet you.

274
00:17:58,475 --> 00:18:01,899
I'm Inukai, the representative. Nice to meet you.
