289
00:19:25,478 --> 00:19:30,838
<i>[Can we discuss about...]</i>

290
00:19:52,476 --> 00:19:54,076
Okay!

291
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,130
<i>[Are you doing well with work?]</i>

292
00:20:03,133 --> 00:20:05,582
<i>[Sorry, I was busy running around the whole day. I get work done somehow.]
[Message has been read]</i>

293
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:19,100
All right.

294
00:20:36,490 --> 00:20:39,693
<i>I'll get going first. Call me when you reach.</i>

295
00:20:39,693 --> 00:20:42,932
<i>- Be careful on your way.
- See you.</i>

296
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:55,951
- <i>We've also graduated from child-rearing duties today.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

297
00:20:55,951 --> 00:21:00,321
- <i>Good job.</i>
- <i>Good job.</i>

298
00:21:00,321 --> 00:21:03,029
<i>By the way, about Kyoka-</i>

299
00:21:03,029 --> 00:21:05,431
<i>After she gets married.</i>

300
00:21:07,350 --> 00:21:10,290
<i>Let's do it after she gets married.</i>

301
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,833
<i>Okay, then.</i>

302
00:21:21,390 --> 00:21:23,589
If...

303
00:21:24,370 --> 00:21:27,421
I get married before her,

304
00:21:27,421 --> 00:21:29,390
what should I do?

305
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:34,259
I'm saying "what if".

306
00:21:35,180 --> 00:21:38,221
Just, "what if".

307
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:41,359
I'm home.

308
00:21:43,590 --> 00:21:47,386
Jeez, you didn't turn the lights on again.

309
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:50,277
You're acting strange.

310
00:21:50,277 --> 00:21:52,550
No, I'm not.

311
00:21:53,140 --> 00:21:55,372
I was just deep in thought.

312
00:21:55,372 --> 00:21:57,431
Deep in thought.

313
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:10,002
We're coming in.

314
00:22:17,490 --> 00:22:20,916
- Hello.
- Hello.

315
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:25,044
Both of you already know each other?

316
00:22:25,044 --> 00:22:27,792
Speaking of knowing each other,

317
00:22:27,792 --> 00:22:31,483
we met because she had been treating me for my back pain.

318
00:22:31,483 --> 00:22:35,649
So sitting here right now makes me all the more awkward.

319
00:22:35,649 --> 00:22:36,976
I'm sorry about that.

320
00:22:36,976 --> 00:22:40,326
Don't be. It's important for us to practice.

321
00:22:40,326 --> 00:22:42,779
- Practice?
- Yes.

322
00:22:42,779 --> 00:22:46,422
Well... Ms. Hinata,

323
00:22:47,170 --> 00:22:49,217
what are you hobbies?

324
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,810
You're wrong.

325
00:22:51,810 --> 00:22:54,775
- Pardon?
- This is not practice.

326
00:22:54,775 --> 00:22:56,475
But...

327
00:22:58,445 --> 00:23:03,043
Will you... go out with me?

328
00:23:04,390 --> 00:23:05,798
What?

329
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,911
Oh, I get it.

330
00:23:12,911 --> 00:23:14,590
I see.

331
00:23:14,590 --> 00:23:17,869
I thought you were interested in my body.

332
00:23:19,930 --> 00:23:24,211
N-No... I mean, my bones. She said my skeleton is rareー

333
00:23:24,211 --> 00:23:25,671
Skeleton?

334
00:23:25,671 --> 00:23:31,751
That's right. There's a miraculous kind of beauty in Sawada-san's shoulder blades.

335
00:23:31,751 --> 00:23:33,096
Thank you.

336
00:23:33,096 --> 00:23:36,187
But that's not all.

337
00:23:36,187 --> 00:23:41,374
I've also questioned myself many times and affirmed it.

338
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:48,646
Sure, there are younger people out there who share the same values as me,

339
00:23:48,646 --> 00:23:52,271
so why must it be Sawada-san, who's a much older senior

340
00:23:52,271 --> 00:23:55,809
with back pain issues and needs aged care in future?

341
00:23:55,809 --> 00:23:57,427
So...

342
00:23:59,030 --> 00:24:01,769
I spoke too much! I'm so sorry!

343
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:08,534
Well, if you'll excuse us, we will take our leave from here.

344
00:24:08,534 --> 00:24:10,536
That's right.

345
00:24:10,536 --> 00:24:12,579
I'm so sorry...

346
00:24:12,579 --> 00:24:16,246
- We'll leave you to have a good chat. Please excuse us.
- Please excuse us.

347
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:25,932
I couldn't find the right words to express how I felt,

348
00:24:25,932 --> 00:24:28,461
so I tried looking up the dictionary.

349
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,878
In the section under "love",

350
00:24:31,878 --> 00:24:34,309
it states "liking someone and wanting to meet him or her".

351
00:24:34,309 --> 00:24:36,546
"An unfulfilled desire

352
00:24:36,546 --> 00:24:39,851
of wanting to stay with someone forever".

353
00:24:39,851 --> 00:24:42,582
I was the one who wrote that.

354
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:46,736
I certainly have this unfulfilled desire

355
00:24:46,736 --> 00:24:50,502
of wanting to see you more, to chat with you more.

356
00:24:51,510 --> 00:24:53,177
That...

357
00:24:54,550 --> 00:24:56,849
is probably love.

358
00:24:59,130 --> 00:25:01,015
But at the same time,

359
00:25:02,130 --> 00:25:07,208
when I am with you, that desire of mine is fulfilled.

360
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:11,771
So that's the part where I don't really understand.

361
00:25:11,771 --> 00:25:14,255
I will bring this up for discussion in the next review.

362
00:25:14,255 --> 00:25:17,341
No, that's not what I mean.

363
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:21,205
Gosh, how should I put it?

364
00:25:21,205 --> 00:25:23,046
Let's see...

365
00:25:23,550 --> 00:25:25,792
You see, Iー

366
00:25:25,792 --> 00:25:27,528
I totally get it.

367
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,354
I get it.

368
00:25:32,930 --> 00:25:35,949
I was just... a little shaken.

369
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:46,258
I'm sorry.

370
00:25:48,350 --> 00:25:51,392
Please put this on hold for now.

371
00:26:02,210 --> 00:26:05,972
This will be my last lesson today.

372
00:26:09,140 --> 00:26:14,025
I'll feel very sad to leave this studio.

373
00:26:14,025 --> 00:26:20,058
However, our bodies, and our hearts,

374
00:26:20,058 --> 00:26:22,572
will change with time.

375
00:26:24,010 --> 00:26:26,776
I hope that I can welcome a new world,

376
00:26:27,820 --> 00:26:33,282
and discover a new me.

377
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:37,627
Work hard, Kyoka Sensei.

378
00:26:37,627 --> 00:26:41,033
All right, let's start with the breathing exercises as usual.

379
00:26:44,900 --> 00:26:47,000
- You've worked hard!
- Thank you.

380
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:49,998
Another great lesson in your own way.

381
00:26:51,040 --> 00:26:53,309
Thank you.

382
00:26:53,309 --> 00:26:55,228
Mikako Sensei?

383
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:03,868
If you keep finding something in your own way, you'll be unhappy.

384
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:07,552
Good luck!

385
00:27:13,020 --> 00:27:15,457
Thank you.

386
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:20,401
You're really something, Kyoka-san. You got away with everything.

387
00:27:20,401 --> 00:27:22,850
- I want to learn from you!
- What?

388
00:27:22,850 --> 00:27:27,120
Be it going independent, or romancing a single father... everything!

389
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:30,148
But between work and family,

390
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:33,752
we've agreed to prioritize the one that's important to us.

391
00:27:33,752 --> 00:27:36,543
That's why we can hardly see each other,

392
00:27:36,543 --> 00:27:38,834
and we're cautious about disturbing each other on the phone.

393
00:27:38,834 --> 00:27:40,807
I guess so.

394
00:27:40,807 --> 00:27:43,912
Riho-san, how can you listen to all this so calmly?

395
00:27:43,912 --> 00:27:47,007
You ordered tea today? Come on, drink with us.

396
00:27:47,007 --> 00:27:49,839
Nah, I had a drop too much yesterday.

397
00:27:49,839 --> 00:27:53,902
Living in your own way means you don't have the freedom to get married.

398
00:27:53,902 --> 00:27:55,496
In my own way?

399
00:27:55,496 --> 00:27:59,966
You're trying to balance both sides, that's why you set this rule, right?

400
00:27:59,966 --> 00:28:02,836
- Yeah.
- I can't do that.

401
00:28:02,836 --> 00:28:06,140
I've thrown away all of Kazuma's outdoor equipment.

402
00:28:06,140 --> 00:28:09,056
- What? His tent, and everything?
- Everything.

403
00:28:09,056 --> 00:28:12,446
He may be staying at home with me now,

404
00:28:12,446 --> 00:28:14,361
but Kazuma doesn't seem happy.

405
00:28:14,361 --> 00:28:17,291
I think my plan has failed...

406
00:28:17,291 --> 00:28:19,540
That's why you're so unsettled today.

407
00:28:19,540 --> 00:28:22,669
Kyoka, if your boyfriend is like Suzu's,

408
00:28:22,669 --> 00:28:26,070
and tells you not to go independent, will you break up?

409
00:28:26,070 --> 00:28:29,185
Well, I don't think...

410
00:28:30,627 --> 00:28:32,920
<i>[Chamber of Commerce and Industry, Kawagoe Prefecture]</i>

411
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:35,722
Regarding group dating for seniors, the locals are active people.

412
00:28:35,722 --> 00:28:37,571
They can even do it while walking around town.

413
00:28:37,571 --> 00:28:39,294
It will also be good publicity for the area.

414
00:28:39,294 --> 00:28:41,655
- I see.
- Yup.

415
00:28:41,655 --> 00:28:43,658
Well, then...

416
00:28:46,890 --> 00:28:48,362
Huh?

417
00:28:48,362 --> 00:28:51,100
Please excuse me for a moment.

418
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:55,023
Hello? This is Higashimura.

419
00:28:55,023 --> 00:28:57,564
Nijiro-kun is having a fever.

420
00:28:57,564 --> 00:29:01,306
It was over 37 degrees Celsius, and we've been monitoring him,

421
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:03,742
but his temperature is now 38 degrees Celsius.

422
00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:07,320
<i>Children may seem fine even if they have a fever, but...</i>

423
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:10,732
I understand. I'll pick him up as soon as possible.

424
00:29:10,732 --> 00:29:13,690
I'm not near the area right now, so it won't be that soon.

425
00:29:13,690 --> 00:29:17,593
I'll let you know again the time I can reach there.

426
00:29:17,593 --> 00:29:19,550
Bye.

427
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:26,060
<i>[Anna]</i>

428
00:29:31,050 --> 00:29:33,610
<i>Please leave your message on the answering machine</i>

429
00:29:33,610 --> 00:29:36,520
<i>after the beep.</i>

430
00:29:38,794 --> 00:29:39,834
<i>[The weather is great!]</i>

431
00:29:39,834 --> 00:29:41,636
<i>[Sent you a picture of it.]</i>

432
00:29:50,170 --> 00:29:53,088
If possible, I hope that you can sponsor

433
00:29:53,088 --> 00:29:56,423
the cost of the monitor for this panel for six months.

434
00:29:56,423 --> 00:30:00,193
I'm sorry, but I'm not in a position give you an answer for that.

435
00:30:00,193 --> 00:30:03,386
Inukai is currently in a meeting. Let me go check with him.

436
00:30:03,386 --> 00:30:05,818
Sure, thank you.

437
00:30:12,150 --> 00:30:13,926
Hello?

438
00:30:15,020 --> 00:30:16,526
Yes.

439
00:30:19,290 --> 00:30:20,348
What?

440
00:30:20,348 --> 00:30:22,957
I want to pick him up as soon as possible,

441
00:30:22,957 --> 00:30:25,902
but I'm in Kawagoe right now, and it'll take some time.

442
00:30:25,902 --> 00:30:28,722
I know that this breaches the rule between us, but...

443
00:30:28,722 --> 00:30:34,600
What are you talking about? I'll go pick Nijiro-kun up right now.

444
00:30:34,600 --> 00:30:38,519
Sorry, and thanks so much.

445
00:30:38,519 --> 00:30:39,682
Okay.

446
00:30:39,682 --> 00:30:43,315
Got it. Bye.

447
00:30:43,315 --> 00:30:45,441
Sorry to keep you waiting.

448
00:30:45,441 --> 00:30:46,941
Please sit.

449
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:52,639
I've heard about your request regarding the monitor.

450
00:30:52,639 --> 00:30:56,683
We'll need to look at the detailed figures for a bit. Are you okay to discuss it now?

451
00:30:57,340 --> 00:30:59,991
It's not really a good time right now.

452
00:30:59,991 --> 00:31:03,592
I'm sorry, but I have an urgent matter to attend to.

453
00:31:03,592 --> 00:31:05,678
I am very sorry.

454
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:12,786
Sawada-san, this is just my opinion,

455
00:31:12,786 --> 00:31:17,138
but to succeed, you must not get your priorities wrong.

456
00:31:17,138 --> 00:31:20,864
I don't know what matter you have to attend to, but to you,

457
00:31:20,864 --> 00:31:24,856
isn't it your priority right now to discuss your request with me?

458
00:31:33,780 --> 00:31:37,091
Sorry, could you excuse me for a moment?

459
00:31:38,830 --> 00:31:43,707
We've settled on the stocks. Can you affirm your commitment to lease them for one year?

460
00:31:45,750 --> 00:31:47,452
Sawada-san?

461
00:31:48,970 --> 00:31:52,212
Erm... I'm very sorry.

462
00:31:52,212 --> 00:31:56,306
Could I excuse myself for today, after all?

463
00:31:58,500 --> 00:32:00,411
I am very sorry.

464
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,552
How's Nijiro-kun?

465
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:13,725
Kyoka-chan.

466
00:32:13,725 --> 00:32:15,379
Thanks.

467
00:32:15,379 --> 00:32:18,740
Fuwa Sensei also brought him to the hospital.

468
00:32:19,850 --> 00:32:22,196
<i>Thank you.</i>

469
00:32:22,196 --> 00:32:24,534
<i>Shall we?</i>

470
00:32:24,534 --> 00:32:27,156
I'm glad it's just a common flu.

471
00:32:27,156 --> 00:32:29,082
I'm free anyway.

472
00:32:29,082 --> 00:32:31,153
Hayate...

473
00:32:34,570 --> 00:32:37,187
Thank you so much for your help.

474
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:41,903
On the way home, Nijiro-kun said he's fine.

475
00:32:42,710 --> 00:32:46,150
He told me he doesn't want to bother his dad and mom.

476
00:32:48,130 --> 00:32:50,488
I'm not trying to lecture you.

477
00:32:50,488 --> 00:32:54,201
I just wanted to tell you that Nijiro is a kind boy

478
00:32:54,201 --> 00:32:57,501
who knows that his parents are working hard for him.

479
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:02,994
If something like this happens again, don't hesitate to call me.

480
00:33:02,994 --> 00:33:05,702
My working hours are flexible.

481
00:33:06,270 --> 00:33:09,282
I'll get going then. See you.

482
00:33:17,860 --> 00:33:21,383
Sorry. I did promise that I'll go pick him up.

483
00:33:21,383 --> 00:33:24,644
Don't be. Thanks for helping to call Fuwa Sensei.

484
00:33:24,644 --> 00:33:27,490
He was able to pick him up earlier than we do.

485
00:33:28,880 --> 00:33:31,336
Is there anything you need?

486
00:33:31,336 --> 00:33:35,721
I'll buy some drinks and Nijiro's favorite food.

487
00:33:35,721 --> 00:33:37,911
In that case, can I trouble you?

488
00:33:37,911 --> 00:33:40,347
"Strawberry yogurt".

489
00:33:41,074 --> 00:33:43,430
Maybe egg tofu, too.

490
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:46,510
"Egg tofu"...

491
00:33:49,460 --> 00:33:53,921
- How's Niji?
- It's just the flu. He's sleeping now.

492
00:34:04,230 --> 00:34:06,603
Kyoka-san, come in...

493
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,718
Takamizawa-san?

494
00:34:12,520 --> 00:34:13,820
Huh?

495
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:24,550
<i>[Cooling Patches]</i>

496
00:34:31,860 --> 00:34:34,003
He's sound asleep.

497
00:34:35,720 --> 00:34:38,782
His fever should subside after sleeping through the night.

498
00:34:49,350 --> 00:34:51,212
I'm sorry.

499
00:34:52,770 --> 00:34:57,009
I knew about the both of you, but I kept quiet about it.

500
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:08,880
But you see, I did get a bit of fun out of that.

501
00:35:17,580 --> 00:35:21,496
I also like you, Kyoka-san.

502
00:35:21,496 --> 00:35:24,558
I feel that you will succeed, given your passion in your work,

503
00:35:24,558 --> 00:35:26,677
and I want to cheer you on.

504
00:35:29,970 --> 00:35:31,727
But...

505
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:34,735
if you don't plan to become a mother,

506
00:35:34,735 --> 00:35:38,004
I hope you won't get involved only half-heartedly with Nijiro.

507
00:35:39,840 --> 00:35:41,041
You're mistaken.

508
00:35:41,041 --> 00:35:43,458
- Kyoka-san is-
- Let me finish.

509
00:35:44,370 --> 00:35:47,107
You are free to date and have fun.

510
00:35:49,970 --> 00:35:52,872
But if you remarry,

511
00:35:52,872 --> 00:35:55,651
I'm just being selfish here...

512
00:35:58,060 --> 00:36:01,616
I want it to be someone who can be a good mother to Nijiro.

513
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:05,372
Someone better than me.

514
00:36:10,300 --> 00:36:13,887
In this day and age, in this country,

515
00:36:13,887 --> 00:36:18,068
it's hard for women to manage on all fronts.

516
00:36:18,740 --> 00:36:21,086
To shoulder everything alone

517
00:36:21,086 --> 00:36:23,518
is a huge undertaking.

518
00:36:24,860 --> 00:36:26,928
I...

519
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:35,799
couldn't do that.

520
00:36:40,010 --> 00:36:44,441
Please think about it carefully.

521
00:36:46,510 --> 00:36:48,425
I hope you can do that.

522
00:36:52,020 --> 00:36:53,425
Got it.

523
00:36:59,010 --> 00:37:00,990
Thanks for your help.

524
00:37:22,060 --> 00:37:23,562
I'm sorry.

525
00:37:25,780 --> 00:37:29,299
But... I have to speak my mind.

526
00:37:34,410 --> 00:37:36,828
Take up that job offer in Osaka.

527
00:37:37,540 --> 00:37:38,841
What?

528
00:37:39,730 --> 00:37:41,337
It's okay.

529
00:37:42,470 --> 00:37:45,903
Except, I have a request.

530
00:37:52,110 --> 00:37:53,690
You were home?

531
00:37:53,690 --> 00:37:55,996
But you didn't turn the lights on.

532
00:37:57,080 --> 00:38:00,544
Yeah, there's a lot on my mind.

533
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:15,073
I...

534
00:38:18,930 --> 00:38:23,333
really... want to find it.

535
00:38:25,750 --> 00:38:28,578
The new me.

536
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,898
But what in the world is that?

537
00:38:43,990 --> 00:38:47,264
When I kept thinking about the person I love,

538
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:52,369
night came before I knew it.

539
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:59,150
I'm no different from you, Dad.

540
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:04,108
Well, I'm not really...

541
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:10,127
I forgot to tell you this.

542
00:39:15,650 --> 00:39:21,478
If you... have found...

543
00:39:21,478 --> 00:39:23,784
your new world,

544
00:39:26,180 --> 00:39:28,255
I'll give you my blessing.

545
00:39:34,340 --> 00:39:36,030
Kyoka.

546
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:48,242
It's Seita-san.

547
00:39:58,060 --> 00:40:00,788
Higashimura Seita-san.

548
00:40:10,260 --> 00:40:12,481
He's the person I love.

549
00:40:19,180 --> 00:40:26,170
♫ <i>I walk alone on my way back home</i> ♫

550
00:40:26,170 --> 00:40:30,980
♫ <i>The song coming from my headphones</i> ♫

551
00:40:30,980 --> 00:40:32,770
♫ <i>Only belongs to us</i> ♫

552
00:40:32,770 --> 00:40:37,555
If possible, I hope you'll give me your blessing.

553
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:43,210
♫ <i>You taught me about small fortunes</i> ♫

554
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:47,270
♫ <i>Looking back at the partly cut off photo</i> ♫

555
00:40:47,270 --> 00:40:48,843
Sure.

556
00:40:48,843 --> 00:40:55,690
♫ <i>Showing you from behind</i> ♫

557
00:40:55,690 --> 00:40:57,440
♫ <i>Who knows how long</i> ♫

558
00:40:57,440 --> 00:40:59,346
Good night.

559
00:41:01,730 --> 00:41:07,580
♫ <i>I already have only you in my eyes</i> ♫

560
00:41:07,580 --> 00:41:13,080
♫ <i>No matter how far away and small the corner may be</i> ♫

561
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:19,760
♫ <i>I bring it into focus</i> ♫

562
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:25,310
♫ <i>Even your slovenly swaying back</i> ♫

563
00:41:25,310 --> 00:41:30,015
♫ <i>Or that smiling face you show when you turn around</i> ♫

564
00:41:30,015 --> 00:41:35,822
<i>[How's Nijiro feeling? Let's meet and talk.]</i>

565
00:41:35,822 --> 00:41:41,030
♫ <i>I want to memorize one of those without complaining</i> ♫

566
00:41:55,830 --> 00:41:58,252
Kyoka-san. Sorry to keep you waiting.

567
00:41:58,252 --> 00:41:59,411
No.

568
00:41:59,411 --> 00:42:02,025
Well, how's Nijiro-kun?

569
00:42:02,025 --> 00:42:04,195
He's feeling much better.

570
00:42:04,195 --> 00:42:06,727
I'm sorry that I've caused all this trouble.

571
00:42:06,727 --> 00:42:08,227
Don't be.

572
00:42:10,100 --> 00:42:12,011
Shall we?

573
00:42:12,011 --> 00:42:13,511
Sure.

574
00:42:21,900 --> 00:42:24,696
Huh? No way.
<i>[Notice of Temporary Closure]</i>

575
00:42:25,590 --> 00:42:29,311
I-I-I'm so sorry! I'll look for another venue right now.

576
00:42:29,311 --> 00:42:30,808
No, it's not your fault.

577
00:42:30,808 --> 00:42:32,980
No, I'm sorry.

578
00:42:33,750 --> 00:42:36,200
Thank you.

579
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:38,430
Please take it.

580
00:42:49,410 --> 00:42:51,726
Hot, hot...

581
00:42:51,726 --> 00:42:54,772
- Did you take the smaller one?
- I don't think so.

582
00:42:54,772 --> 00:42:56,675
- Let's dig in.
- Let's dig in.

583
00:42:56,675 --> 00:42:59,119
This place is still better, after all.

584
00:42:59,119 --> 00:43:01,250
This is better, indeed.

585
00:43:07,910 --> 00:43:09,410
It's hot?

586
00:43:15,280 --> 00:43:16,883
Hot!

587
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:22,903
- It's delicious.
- Yup. Delicious.

588
00:43:24,650 --> 00:43:26,151
It's hot.

589
00:43:28,190 --> 00:43:29,695
Hot.

590
00:43:35,590 --> 00:43:38,719
That person's name is called Inukai,

591
00:43:38,719 --> 00:43:43,058
but he always wears a T-shirt with cat prints, so I was rather amused.

592
00:43:43,058 --> 00:43:46,212
I've been wanting to tell you about that,

593
00:43:46,212 --> 00:43:47,884
but I didn't want to text you only for that.

594
00:43:47,884 --> 00:43:49,976
I really don't mind if you do.

595
00:43:49,976 --> 00:43:54,341
Such things only have meaning if we meet and talk about it. Don't you think so?

596
00:43:54,341 --> 00:43:55,653
Meet?

597
00:43:55,653 --> 00:43:58,441
That's right. We meet.

598
00:44:03,570 --> 00:44:06,257
Oh, we're closed for the day.

599
00:44:09,343 --> 00:44:14,543
<i>[Attention: Hinata Akari-sama]</i>
<i>[Notice of Result of Medical Examination]</i>

600
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:32,361
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

601
00:44:32,361 --> 00:44:34,529
Sawada-san?

602
00:44:35,100 --> 00:44:37,021
What's wrong?

603
00:44:37,650 --> 00:44:39,655
Well...

604
00:44:44,030 --> 00:44:46,072
I...

605
00:44:46,072 --> 00:44:47,630
Yes?

606
00:44:48,620 --> 00:44:51,376
I'm turning down your request to go out.

607
00:45:05,170 --> 00:45:07,032
Kyoka-san.

608
00:45:18,610 --> 00:45:20,832
Feels good, doesn't it?

609
00:45:29,090 --> 00:45:30,922
Seita-san.

610
00:45:33,150 --> 00:45:40,880
credits

611
00:45:45,330 --> 00:45:47,196
Will you

612
00:45:48,910 --> 00:45:51,582
go out with me,

613
00:45:51,582 --> 00:45:54,413
with marriage in mind?

614
00:46:03,850 --> 00:46:05,843
I'm sorry.

615
00:46:09,700 --> 00:46:13,491
Let's... end it.

616
00:46:16,260 --> 00:46:22,130
♫ <i>You're in the center of my eyes</i> ♫

617
00:46:22,130 --> 00:46:24,537
Kyoka-chan, you are my miracle.
[The love turmoil reaches its climax...]
[Preview]

618
00:46:24,537 --> 00:46:27,029
I would like to continue my life together with you.
<i> [The love turmoil reaches its climax...]</i>

619
00:46:27,029 --> 00:46:28,459
I guess we won't meet anymore.
<i>[The love turmoil reaches its climax...]</i>

620
00:46:28,459 --> 00:46:29,890
It's not possible for you.
<i>[The love turmoil reaches its climax...]</i>

621
00:46:29,890 --> 00:46:32,726
I did it on purpose. Let's get married.
